\b 3.1. Requirements Overview\par
\b0
This chapter defines the software requirements of the current FF3D game build from the perspective of the implemented system. The purpose of the chapter is to translate the business and operational context established in Chapter 2 into a structured set of system requirements that can be mapped to existing modules, runtime flows, and testable behaviors.\par

The current game is a simulation-oriented single-player PC application in which the player moves through a connected training loop: profile selection, level and scenario selection, Call Phase interaction, payload-driven transition, on-site mission execution, and mission-end review. Because the product is a game rather than a conventional transactional information system, the requirements must be expressed not only in terms of data handling, but also in terms of scene flow, user interaction, mission state, equipment behavior, and runtime feedback.\par

For the current build, the requirement scope is limited to the implemented MVP baseline. The active software scope includes Main Menu, local player profile flow, Loading Scene, Level Select, Call Phase, on-site mission scenes, objective and fail-condition tracking, local result persistence, minimap, equipment use, bot commands, and mission-end summary. Multiplayer, online infrastructure, cloud synchronization, VR deployment, and institutional training management features remain outside the current scope.\par

