\b 3.2. User Classes and Actors\par
\b0
The current build has one primary runtime actor: the player. The player is the direct software user who launches the game, selects or continues a local profile, chooses a scenario, completes the Call Phase, performs the on-site mission, and reviews the mission result.\par

In addition to the player, there are non-runtime stakeholder classes relevant to the engineering and evaluation context of the project. These include instructors, academic reviewers, project supervisors, and the development team. However, these roles are not implemented as separate in-game permission classes. The game does not provide authenticated access roles, remote administration, or instructor-side runtime interfaces.\par

Therefore, this chapter uses the following distinction:\par

Player: the primary runtime actor.\par
Instructor / Evaluator: external stakeholder class for academic or training usage.\par
Developer / QA Reviewer: engineering support stakeholder class, not a normal gameplay actor.\par

