\b 3.6. Use Case Overview\par
\b0
The use case model of the current game should be kept focused on real runtime interactions rather than hypothetical training-management features. The main actor is the player, and the core use cases are centered on selecting a scenario, interacting with the Call Phase, entering the mission, using gameplay systems, and reviewing results.\par

\b 3.6.1. Actors\par
\b0
The main actor of the current system is the player. Supporting stakeholder classes such as developer or evaluator may observe outputs such as progress records or result data, but they do not participate as alternate runtime actors in the normal gameplay loop.\par

